The paper deals with coinductive structures and probabilistic streams and trees, which are topics typically studied in the areas of logic (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses a reduction to model-checking pCTL* formulas on probabilistic pushdown automata, which falls under the category of formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). Additionally, the paper involves the use of coalgebraic semantics, which is a topic studied in the area of data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses decidability results, which is a topic studied in the area of computational complexity (cs.LT).
